author: Inside Edition
description: Inside Edition's former longtime host Deborah Norville is back on TV hosting a new game show. Norville showed Inside Edition the set of her new game show, "The Perfect Line." Norville had a storied career at Inside Edition covering the world's biggest stories. Now, three months after saying her goodbye, she is opening up about her new chapter. Norville, who started her career as a reporter in Atlanta, Georgia, says she is happy to be back in Atlanta all these years later.
title: Inside Edition's Deborah Norville Back on TV With New Game Show

author: Inside Edition
description: Video shows a police officer and his K9 getting dragged by a fleeing car. The Lake Wales Police Department in Florida says it happened when an officer tried to make a traffic stop. They say the driver pulled into a gas station and exited the car, asking the officer why he was being pulled over. Police say when approached by the officer, the driver got back into the vehicle and took off with the officer and K9 entangled in the car. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Officer and K9 Dragged by Fleeing Car in Florida: Cops
